# | Statement | Definition                                                                                                           | Example                                                                                                   | Output              |
# | --------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------- |
# | **if**    | Jab condition **True** ho to code chalega. Agar **False** ho to skip ho jaayega.                                     | `python x = 10 if x > 5:     print("x is greater than 5") `                                               | x is greater than 5 |
# | **elif**  | Agar pehli condition False ho jaaye to doosri (extra) condition check karta hai. Multiple `elif` use kar sakte hain. | `python x = -3 if x > 0:     print("Positive") elif x < 0:     print("Negative") `                        | Negative            |
# | **else**  | Agar upar ki saari conditions False ho jaayein to `else` block chalega.                                              | `python x = 0 if x > 0:     print("Positive") elif x < 0:     print("Negative") else:     print("Zero") ` | Zero                |
